<refentry id="MGR-DROPHBA">
  <refmeta>
    <refentrytitle>DROP HBA</refentrytitle>
    <manvolnum>7</manvolnum>
    <refmiscinfo>Manage - Language Statements</refmiscinfo>
  </refmeta>

  <refnamediv>
    <refname>DROP HBA</refname>
    <refpurpose>drop the content from the hba table and postgresql.conf, the hba_value format "conntype database user ip mask method".</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>

  <indexterm zone="mgr-drophba">
    <primary>DROP HBA</primary>
  </indexterm>

  <refsynopsisdiv>
  <synopsis>
DROP HBA GTM { ALL | nodename } ( "hba_value" )
DROP HBA COORDINATOR { ALL | nodename } ( "hba_value" )
DROP HBA DATANODE { ALL | nodename } ( "hba_value" )

<phrase>where hba_value must be the following:</phrase>

    host database user IP-address IP-mask auth-method
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
   <command>DROP HBA</command> drop the content to the hba table,and it's alse drop it in pg_hba.conf file.
The hba_value must be the format "conntype database user ip mask method".
    </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>Examples</title>
  <para>
   drop the content to all coordinator's pg_hba.conf file:
<programlisting>
drop hba all("host postgres gz 10.14.23.100 32 trust","host postgres gz 10.14.23.101 24 trust");
</programlisting>
  </para>
  <para>
   drop the content to the specified coordinator's pg_hba.conf file:
<programlisting>
drop hba coord1("host postgres mas 10.1.226.202 32 trust");
</programlisting>
  </para>
  </refsect1>
